extends /sites/Funtower/layouts/base.pug

block variables
    - const title = 'Privacy Policy | Funtower'
    - const description = 'Learn how Funtower protects your privacy and manages your data while you enjoy playing our game. We are committed to ensuring a secure and transparent experience for every player.'

block content
    +Header()

    main
        section.container.privacy-policy
            h1 Privacy Policy for Funtower
            p At Funtower, your privacy and security are our top priorities. We are dedicated to protecting your personal information while providing a fun and engaging gaming experience. This Privacy Policy explains what data we collect, how we use it, and the steps we take to ensure your privacy while using our website. If you have any questions or need more information about this policy, feel free to contact us.

            h2 Information We Collect
            p When you play Funtower, we gather specific technical details to help optimize your gaming experience. This includes information like your IP address, browser type, and the type of device you’re using. We also track gameplay interactions, such as levels completed and in-game actions, to enhance platform performance. None of this information is linked to personally identifiable data.

            h2 Log Files
            p Funtower uses log files to analyze user activity and improve our website. These files collect data such as IP addresses, browser types, Internet Service Providers (ISP), timestamps, and pages visited. This data helps us understand how users interact with the platform and is used solely for technical improvements and analytical purposes.

            h2 Third-Party Services
            p To ensure the best possible experience, Funtower may collaborate with trusted third-party services that assist with performance tracking and platform analytics. These services help us optimize gameplay and user experience without collecting personally identifiable information.

            h2 Advertising Partners
            p Some of our advertising partners may display ads on Funtower and collect non-personal data to show content that’s more relevant to you. Each partner has its own privacy practices, so we encourage you to review their policies before interacting with their content.

            h2 Privacy Policies of Advertising Partners
            p While Funtower works with select advertising partners, we are not responsible for how these third parties handle user data. We recommend reviewing their privacy policies if you wish to learn more about their data practices.

            h2 Data Security
            p We take data protection seriously and use industry-standard security measures to safeguard any information collected. Although no online system is completely secure, we continuously work to strengthen our defenses and protect your data from unauthorized access or misuse.

            h2 User Rights
            p You have the right to view, update, or request the removal of any personal data we may have collected. To exercise these rights or if you have any questions regarding your data, please reach out to our support team.

            h2 Children's Privacy
            p Funtower is intended for users aged 18 and above. We do not knowingly collect or store personal information from individuals under this age. If you believe someone under 18 has provided personal data on our platform, please contact us, and we will take immediate steps to remove the information.

            h2 Data Retention
            p We retain collected data only for as long as necessary to improve user experience and ensure platform stability. Once the data is no longer required, it is either securely deleted or anonymized.

            h2 Online Privacy Only
            p This Privacy Policy applies solely to information collected through Funtower’s website. It does not extend to data gathered through offline methods or any other channels outside our platform.

            h2 Updates to This Privacy Policy
            p We may revise this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect updates in regulations or platform features. We encourage users to check this page periodically to stay informed about how we protect your data.

            h2 Consent
            p By using Funtower, you agree to this Privacy Policy and its terms. If you have any questions or need further clarification regarding our data practices, feel free to contact us.

            p For more information or specific inquiries about our privacy practices, please reach out to our team. We're here to help and ensure your Funtower experience remains safe and enjoyable.



    +Footer()